strength, with steeper laws having stronger bumps. Moreover, the
attenuation curve correlates with specific star formation rate (SFR),
with more active galaxies having shallower dust curves and weaker bumps.
There is also a weak correlation with inclination. The observed trends
can be explained by differences in the dust-to-star geometry, a varying
grain size distribution, or a combination of both. Our results have
several implications for galaxy evolution studies. First, the assumption
